{"type":null,"faqId":35081,"title":" How do I set my phone to work as a modem and provide Internet access for computers?","answer":"<html>\n<head>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\n.s1{font-weight:bold;}\n.s2{display: inline-block; text-indent: 0; min-width: 0.3048611in;}\n.p1{margin-left:1.18125in;margin-top:0.11111111in;margin-bottom:0.11111111in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p2{text-indent:-0.2951389in;margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p3{margin-left:1.18125in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p4{margin-bottom:0.027777778in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Book Antiqua;font-size:9pt;}\n.p5{margin-left:1.4409722in;margin-top:0.027777778in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"b1\">\n<div  >\n<p  >\n<span>If a computer provides a wireless network adapter, you can turn on </span><span class=\"s1\">Portable Wi-Fi hotspot</span><span> as follows: Go to </span><span class=\"s1\">Settings</span><span>. Under </span><span class=\"s1\">Wireless &amp; networks</span><span>, touch </span><span class=\"s1\">More</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Tethering &amp; portable hotspot</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Portable</span><span> </span><span class=\"s1\">Wi-Fi hotspot</span><span>. The computer can then connect to your phone over Wi-Fi to access the Internet.( Currently, this function is available to Windows operating system.)</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s2\">1.  </span><span>On the home screen, touch Settings&gt; Wireless &amp; networks&gt;touch More &gt; Tethering &amp; portable hotspot&gt;Touch USB tethering.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>    </span><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=111428\" style=\"width:1.8645834in;height:3.3263888in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s2\">2.  </span><span>On a computer, use HiSuite to install the USB driver for your phone. Right-click My Computer and choose Manage.</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p4\">\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=111429\" style=\"width:0.59375in;height:0.16805555in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p class=\"p5\">\n<span>When using USB tethering, your phone's mobile data connection must be turned on. Otherwise, your phone cannot provide Internet access for computers.</span>\n</p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":244,"languageName":"mm","faqCode":"9822","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1437034667000,"seriesProductName":"Y541-U02","visitedTimes":1,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"HONOR BEE DUAL SIM ( Y541-U02 )","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}